[src:apache-nifi/apache-nifi] NiFi is a Java program that runs within a Java virtual machine running on a server.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] Data lineage facilitates the ability to replay specific segments or inputs of the dataflow.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] This can be used in debugging or regenerating lost outputs.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] In database systems, this concept is closely related to data provenance, which involves maintaining records of inputs, entities, systems and processes that influence data.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] Data provenance provides a historical record of data origins and transformations.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] Data lineage information includes technical metadata about data transformations.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] Enriched data lineage may include additional elements such as data quality test results, reference data, data models, business terminology, data stewardship information, program management details and enterprise systems associated with data points and transformations.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] Data lineage visualization tools often include masking features that allow users to focus on information relevant to specific use cases.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] To unify representations across disparate systems, metadata normalization or standardization may be required.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] Representation broadly depends on the scope of the metadata management and reference point of interest.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] Data lineage provides sources of the data and intermediate data flow hops from the reference point with **backward data lineage**, leading to the final destination's data points and its intermediate data flows with **forward data lineage**.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] These views can be combined with end-to-end **lineage** for a reference point that provides a complete audit trail of that data point of interest from sources to their final destinations.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] As the data points or hops increase, the complexity of such representation becomes incomprehensible.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] Thus, the best feature of the data lineage view is the ability to simplify the view by temporarily masking unwanted peripheral data points.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] Tools with the masking feature enable scalability of the view and enhance analysis with the best user experience for both technical and business users.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] Data lineage also enables companies to trace sources of specific business data to track errors, implement changes in processes and implementing system migrations to save significant amounts of time and resources.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] Data lineage can improve efficiency in business intelligence BI processes.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] Data lineage can be represented visually to discover the data flow and movement from its source to destination via various changes and hops on its way in the enterprise environment.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] This includes how the data is transformed along the way, how the representation and parameters change and how the data splits or converges after each hop.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] A simple representation of the Data Lineage can be shown with dots and lines, where dots represent data containers for data points, and lines connecting them represent transformations the data undergoes between the data containers.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] Data lineage can be visualized at various levels based on the granularity of the view.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] At a very high-level, data lineage is visualized as systems that the data interacts with before it reaches its destination.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] At its most granular, visualizations at the data point level can provide the details of the data point and its historical behavior, attribute properties and trends and data quality of the data passed through that specific data point in the data lineage.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] The scope of the data lineage determines the volume of metadata required to represent its data lineage.
[src:apache-nifi/data-lineage] Usually, data governance and data management of an organization determine the scope of the data lineage based on their regulations, enterprise data management strategy, data impact, reporting attributes and critical data elements of the organization.
